  m_Name: frontalbone
  m_EditorClassIdentifier: Assembly-CSharp::ModelPartDataSO
  id: frontalbone
  partName: Frontal Bone
  descriptionChunks:
  - The frontal bone forms the front portion of the canine skull and contributes
    to protection of the brain and formation of the orbital cavities. Located between
    the nasal and parietal bones, it provides structural support for the forehead
    and upper facial region. This bone contains portions of the frontal sinuses,
  - which help reduce skull weight and contribute to respiratory resonance. The frontal
    bone also serves as an attachment site for facial muscles and connective tissues
    involved in expression and head movement. Strong structural integrity is essential
    for cranial protection and sensory function.
